Sentencas: The flat-tube high power density (HPD) solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is a geometry based on a tubular type SOFC, and is being developed by Siemens Westinghouse and other international companies in Japan and Korea.
Titulo: Numerical study of a flat-tube high power density solid oxide fuel cell - Part II: Cell performance and stack optimization

Sentencas: It has increased power density, but still maintains the beneficial feature of secure sealing for a tabular SOFC.
Titulo: Numerical study of a flat-tube high power density solid oxide fuel cell - Part II: Cell performance and stack optimization

Sentencas: In this paper, the electric performance of a flat-tube HPD SOFC is studied.
Titulo: Numerical study of a flat-tube high power density solid oxide fuel cell - Part II: Cell performance and stack optimization

Sentencas: This paper also investigates the effects of the stack chamber number, stack shape, and other stack geometry features on the performance of the flat-tube HPD SOFC.
Titulo: Numerical study of a flat-tube high power density solid oxide fuel cell - Part II: Cell performance and stack optimization

Sentencas: The results show that the performance of a flat-tube HPD SOFC is better than a tubular SOFC with the same active cell surface, and that increasing the number of chambers number can improve the overall performance of a flat-tube HPD SOFC.
Titulo: Numerical study of a flat-tube high power density solid oxide fuel cell - Part II: Cell performance and stack optimization

Sentencas: The height of a flat-tube HPD SOFC and the thickness of the ribs do not have much effect on the performance of the cell as is expected.
Titulo: Numerical study of a flat-tube high power density solid oxide fuel cell - Part II: Cell performance and stack optimization

Sentencas: This study will help to design and optimize the flat-tube HPD SOFC.
Titulo: Numerical study of a flat-tube high power density solid oxide fuel cell - Part II: Cell performance and stack optimization
